{"type":"message","id":"963f04ba","parentId":"55be1c80","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:53:39.395Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the full memory chain:\n\n1. **ephemeral**: The hook writes JSONL to `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/` — currently has 5 files\n2. **session-summary**: There's a hook at `/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary` and it generated a summary file at `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-13-session-summary.md` with `<!-- summary-only -->` tag\n3. **MEMORY.md**: Just created at `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main/MEMORY.md`\n\n\n4. **Bootstrap**: The SOUL.md rules should force a read of MEMORY.md on startup, and there's routing logic in `routing_rules.json` that uses classifier labels to determine which agent handles the task.\n\nThe chain is: hook writes to ephemeral, session-summary reads ephemeral and writes to the summary file with the `<!-- summary-only -->` tag, then bootstrap should inject MEMORY.md via SOUL.md rules, but the session-summary hook isn't being triggered. I need to check if the session-summary hook is actually configured in the gateway hooks config.","thinkingSignature":"74b88bb0359b54150b024979aaa534eea082a71b168e01b88a0a264d1a257632"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7f252463724942b4be83a30a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/.openclaw/config.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | grep -A5 -B5 \"summary\\|hook\" | head -80"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_eb0528d0cd9444f9b9765502","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1011,"output":342,"cacheRead":27648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29001,"cost":{"input":0.0003033,"output":0.0004104,"cacheRead":0.00165888,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00237258}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776063209526,"responseId":"062bc5e8905d15c69aec87653ff2aec6"}}
