{"type":"message","id":"3e9b0f8e","parentId":"5437bca6","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:54:34.226Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_88dd69748b9a458082b74860","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"openclaw-cc-bridge\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"model\": \"minimax-m2.5\",\n    \"allowedTools\": [\n      \"Bash\",\n      \"Read\",\n      \"Edit\",\n      \"Write\",\n      \"Glob\",\n      \"Grep\",\n      \"WebFetch\",\n      \"WebSearch\",\n      \"Mildred\",\n      \"Task*\"\n    ],\n    \"env\": {\n      \"ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL\": \"https://zhenze-huhehaote.cmecloud.cn/api/coding/v1\",\n      \"ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"J99ouXWKXO8Zg5tLqv92YVsPNFhwuZc-z6z2ioeg7VE\",\n      \"ANTHROPIC_MODEL\": \"minimax-m2.5\"\n    }\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":58,"aggregated":"{\n  \"openclaw-cc-bridge\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"model\": \"minimax-m2.5\",\n    \"allowedTools\": [\n      \"Bash\",\n      \"Read\",\n      \"Edit\",\n      \"Write\",\n      \"Glob\",\n      \"Grep\",\n      \"WebFetch\",\n      \"WebSearch\",\n      \"Mildred\",\n      \"Task*\"\n    ],\n    \"env\": {\n      \"ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL\": \"https://zhenze-huhehaote.cmecloud.cn/api/coding/v1\",\n      \"ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"J99ouXWKXO8Zg5tLqv92YVsPNFhwuZc-z6z2ioeg7VE\",\n      \"ANTHROPIC_MODEL\": \"minimax-m2.5\"\n    }\n  }\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776063274216}}
{"type":"message","id":"9285d083","parentId":"3e9b0f8e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:54:34.237Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0e8c815c389543e8828e0da0","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/HOOK.md\n---\nname: session-summary\ndescription: \"session 结束时（/new 或 /reset）生成结构化摘要，写入 memory/，供下次 bootstrap 读取。依赖 context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile 读取刚结束的 session 内容。\"\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\": {\n      \"emoji\": \"📝\",\n      \"events\": [\"command:new\", \"command:reset\"],\n      \"requires\": {\n        \"bins\": [\"node\"],\n        \"config\": [\"workspace.dir\"]\n      },\n      \"always\": true\n    }\n  }\n---\n\n# session-summary\n\n每次 `/new` 或 `/reset` 触发时，异步生成刚结束 session 的结构化摘要。\n\n## 行为\n\n- **异步执行**：hook 立即返回，摘要生成在后台，不阻塞命令响应\n- **降级策略**：LLM 不可用或生成失败时，写入规则摘要，不报错不中断\n- **文件格式**：`memory/YYYY-MM-DD-{slug}.md`，带 `<!-- summary-only -->` 标记\n\n## 摘要格式\n\n```markdown\n# Session: {date} {time}\n\n## 主题\n{一句话概括}\n\n## 关键决策\n- {决策1}\n- {决策2}（无则省略）\n\n## 重要发现\n- {发现1}\n- {发现2}（无则省略）\n\n## 待跟进\n- {事项1}\n- {事项2}（无则省略）\n```\n\n## LLM 调用\n\n通过 v8 Router (3102) 调用 LLM 生成摘要，超时 20s。\n\n## Bootstrap 读取\n\nsession 启动时，扫描 `memory/` 下最新摘要文件（按修改时间），读入作为上下文。"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":68,"aggregated":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/HOOK.md\n---\nname: session-summary\ndescription: \"session 结束时（/new 或 /reset）生成结构化摘要，写入 memory/，供下次 bootstrap 读取。依赖 context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile 读取刚结束的 session 内容。\"\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\": {\n      \"emoji\": \"📝\",\n      \"events\": [\"command:new\", \"command:reset\"],\n      \"requires\": {\n        \"bins\": [\"node\"],\n        \"config\": [\"workspace.dir\"]\n      },\n      \"always\": true\n    }\n  }\n---\n\n# session-summary\n\n每次 `/new` 或 `/reset` 触发时，异步生成刚结束 session 的结构化摘要。\n\n## 行为\n\n- **异步执行**：hook 立即返回，摘要生成在后台，不阻塞命令响应\n- **降级策略**：LLM 不可用或生成失败时，写入规则摘要，不报错不中断\n- **文件格式**：`memory/YYYY-MM-DD-{slug}.md`，带 `<!-- summary-only -->` 标记\n\n## 摘要格式\n\n```markdown\n# Session: {date} {time}\n\n## 主题\n{一句话概括}\n\n## 关键决策\n- {决策1}\n- {决策2}（无则省略）\n\n## 重要发现\n- {发现1}\n- {发现2}（无则省略）\n\n## 待跟进\n- {事项1}\n- {事项2}（无则省略）\n```\n\n## LLM 调用\n\n通过 v8 Router (3102) 调用 LLM 生成摘要，超时 20s。\n\n## Bootstrap 读取\n\nsession 启动时，扫描 `memory/` 下最新摘要文件（按修改时间），读入作为上下文。","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776063274226}}
{"type":"message","id":"bfdfb9c9","parentId":"9285d083","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:55:12.574Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. Let me trace the memory链路:\n\n1. **Session ends** (when /new or /reset is called)\n2. **session-summary hook** fires on `command:new` or `command:reset`\n3. It reads the previous session's messages + ephemeral entries\n4. It generates a summary and writes to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD-{slug}.md`\n5. It also promotes entities (creating/updating files in `memory/entities/`)\n\nBut there's a critical issue: the `session-summary` hook is triggered by `command:new` or `command:reset`, but this event only fires on the **new** session (after /new), not the old session that just ended.\n \nLooking at the handler code, it checks for the event type and action, then resolves the session file using the context's `previousSessionEntry` to get the file path from the session that just ended. The problem is that when a user calls /new, the old session's context object may not be properly passed to the hook in the new session's initialization.\n\nI need to trace whether the `command:new` event actually fires with the correct `previousSessionEntry` context in the first place. Let me examine the ephemeral files to see what's actually being captured. Looking at the session context, the classification and scoring metadata are present from the hook processing, but the session summary didn't execute. The event structure shows a `command:new` action with no prior session entry recorded, which means the session summary hook never fired during this /new cycle. The handler is exporting correctly as both default and named exports, so that's not the issue. The real problem might be that `previousSessionEntry` isn't being populated when the new session starts—it could be that the gateway isn't passing the old session's metadata to the new session's context. Or perhaps the hook is actually firing asynchronously and we're just not seeing the result yet. The session-summary hook should trigger after the /new command completes, but the ephemeral entries only captured the \"修复3104\" events without the \"记忆链路没跑通\" exchanges, suggesting the hook may not have executed or didn't properly handle the latest session. The gateway likely sends a `command:new` event to hooks when /new is called, but I need to trace whether context.previousSessionEntry gets populated at that point to understand why the summary didn't capture the full conversation. The hook correctly identifies the event as a command and fires on `command:new`, but I'm noticing the context shows `previousSessionEntry: null` and `sessionEntry: {}` - which might be why the session file path resolution failed. Let me trace through the context structure more carefully to understand what's actually being passed to the hook.\n\nLooking at the context.json content, it has `classification` and `scoring` from the auto-score-classify hook, but there's no session history data - just the current message preview and scoring metadata. The key issue is that `previousSessionEntry` isn't populated, which suggests the hook can't access the previous session's information to write the summary.\n\nWhen /new is called, the new session should receive context about the old session through `context.previousSessionEntry`, but it seems like this isn't happening. The new session only gets classification/scoring data, not the conversation history needed for the session summary to work properly. the summary from the previous session.\n\nFor session-summary to work, the gateway needs to:\n1. Detect /new command\n2. Before closing old session: store session file path in a shared location OR pass it via context\n3. Start new session with context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile set\n\nLet me check if the gateway actually does this by looking at how /new is handled... I can't easily check that without access to gateway source code.\n\nThe more pragmatic approach: instead of trying to fix the complex gateway hook system, I should make the memory chain work through a simpler mechanism:\n- When I end this session, I write the summary myself\n- Or I accept that /new can't preserve the memory chain perfectly and use the cron-based memory keeper as the primary mechanism\n\nActually, looking at the existing architecture more carefully - the session-summary hook fires on `command:new` in the new session context. The `previousSessionEntry` should contain the previous session's metadata. But if it's null, that means the gateway isn't passing the previous session data to new sessions.\n\nThe most likely culprit is that `previousSessionEntry.sessionFile` isn't being populated. I should add logging to the session-summary handler to see what's actually in the context when it fires. Or I could check the session history file directly - `/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/` should have a record of past sessions including their file paths.\n\nBut practically speaking, the user wants this fixed. The session-summary mechanism is the right approach, but something in the gateway isn't connecting the previous session data. I need to verify if previousSessionEntry is actually null when the hook fires, and if so, figure out why the gateway isn't passing that information through. The ephemeral capture is working, but the hook itself might not be firing when /new is called. The most direct solution is to write the summary to MEMORY.md directly at the end of this session, then test whether session-summary actually fires on the next /new. The real issue might be that the hook runs asynchronously after /new completes, so the summary generation happens too late to affect the new session's context. the new session starts).\n\nSince session-summary is async (doesn't block), the new session might start before the summary is written.\n\nLet me check if there's a timing issue - does the new session wait for session-summary to complete before starting? If not, the new session won't have the summary.\n\nBut that's a gateway behavior issue, not something I can fix from here.\n\nActually, let me just accept that the session-summary mechanism has issues and focus on making the memory chain work through other means:\n1. The cron-based memory keeper already runs daily at 4am\n2. The SOUL.md bootstrap rule forces reading MEMORY.md\n3. I've already written MEMORY.md\n\nFor the session-summary to work properly, the gateway needs to pass `previousSessionEntry` correctly, which requires a code fix.\n\nGiven the complexity, let me just document the issue and provide a workaround. The user wants me to \"跑通\" the memory chain, but the core problem is that the gateway isn't passing session context between sessions. Without fixing that code, session-summary can't read the old session's file path. The most pragmatic approach is to ensure MEMORY.md gets written at the end of each session as a fallback, even if session-summary fails. , when /new is called in the current session, the gateway creates a new session and fires `command:new` event with context about the new session, but it should also include `previousSessionEntry` with the old session's info. If that's null, the gateway isn't providing it.\n\nI think the real issue is timing—the hook runs after /new completes, but the new session might start before the summary finishes writing. The hook itself is async and non-blocking, so the new session begins immediately without waiting for the summary file to be created. The solution would be either making the hook synchronous or having the new session wait for completion. These are gateway-level fixes I can't implement from here, so I need to work around the timing issue instead. The real issue is that session-summary is async and non-blocking, so it fires but doesn't wait for the summary to be written before the new session starts. I could add a delay mechanism, but the core problem is that previousSessionEntry might not be populated by the gateway when the new session initializes. Let me focus on what I can actually test and verify from my end. the new session\n3. Session-summary fires, but can't read the old session file because previousSessionEntry is null\n\nThis creates a catch-22: the session summary needs the old session's data to generate a summary, but that data isn't available when it runs. Meanwhile, the new session starts without waiting for the summary to complete, so even if the hook could write the summary, the new session would already be initialized.\n\nThe solution would require either making the hook synchronous or having the gateway pass the previous session entry before the new session starts—both are gateway-level changes. I should focus on what I can actually test and verify: confirming whether the hook fires, whether previousSessionEntry is populated, and whether the summary gets written, then document what needs to be fixed at the gateway level. I need to trace through the session lifecycle to understand when previousSessionEntry gets populated. The hook receives a context object that should contain previousSessionEntry, but I need to verify whether this is actually being passed through correctly or if it's arriving as null. Rather than trying to fix the gateway code, I should add diagnostic logging to the session-summary hook itself to see what's actually in the context when it runs.","thinkingSignature":"63823757e5717ea70dcc1bc91e8607572e0b54cd5ecb075032e3a5c503332b96"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n现在清楚了。让我追踪断点：\n\n**链路现状：**\n- `ephemeral/` ✅ 在积累\n- `session-summary` hook ✅ 存在（监听 `command:new`）\n- `handler.js` ✅ 正确（export default + module.exports）\n- `previousSessionEntry` ❓ 未知（可能是 null）\n\n让我检查 gateway 是否在 /new 时传递了旧 session 信息：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_70f37a670cfb4c63887c7473","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/ai/.openclaw -name \"context.json\" -exec sh -c 'echo \"=== {} ===\"; cat \"{}\" | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=js