{"type":"message","id":"7cecb61d","parentId":"f6cd1e1d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:55:35.057Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The context.json doesn't have previousSessionEntry or sessionEntry in the top level. These fields might be passed directly to the hook event object, not stored in context.json.\n\nThe issue is clear now:\n1. session-summary hook listens for `command:new`\n2. When /new is triggered, the gateway passes an event to hooks\n3. The event should contain `context.previousSessionEntry` with the old session's file path\n4. The hook reads that file to extract messages, then generates a summary\n\nThe question is: does the gateway actually pass `previousSessionEntry` with the session file path?\n\nLet me think about what I need to do:\n1. The hook code expects `event.context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile` to exist\n2. If the gateway doesn't pass this, the hook falls back to reading nothing\n\n\n3. I should test the /new flow end-to-end to verify whether the gateway is actually providing the previous session data\n\nThe easiest approach is to run a test /new and check if a summary file gets created, then verify if the session file path is being passed correctly by examining the gateway's actual event payload.","thinkingSignature":"718dc340fdb635f87926831a6fa879b1504f3f930aec6a8ca62904b77738a903"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n断点找到了。context.json 里没有 `previousSessionEntry` 字段——gateway 传给 hook 的 event 里才有这个字段，但 session-summary hook 需要它来找到旧 session 文件。\n\n让我验证一下 /new 到底有没有触发 hook 写摘要：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ed0f64ae12df4ca0a7a09599","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/*.md 2>/dev/null | tail -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":402,"output":335,"cacheRead":52096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52833,"cost":{"input":0.00012059999999999999,"output":0.00040199999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0031257599999999996