{"type":"message","id":"9a371714","parentId":"bd3e528e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:55:49.949Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_6afaf2c9620b479f9b64e5e6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-04-13 13:00\n\n<!-- summary-only -->\n\n## 主题\n框架修复与两层记忆系统部署\n\n## 关键决策\n1. 3104 classifier 替换为 workspace Apr 13 新版，修好 numpy 序列化 bug\n2. 3103 scorer 加 text 字段兼容层\n3. openclaw-router 判定为半成品，disable systemd service\n4. 重新配置 cron：wiki-auto-learn 每小时，memory-keeper/memory-maintain 每天\n5. 实现两层记忆系统：hook 实时写入 ephemeral/ + session-summary LLM 提炼\n\n## 重要发现\n1. 3104 classifier 500 错误根因：numpy.float32 无法 JSON 序列化，修复只需类型转换\n2. 3103 scorer 只认 prompt 不认 text，gateway hook 发的 text 被忽略\n3. openclaw-router 核心依赖缺失，不是配置问题，是代码不完整\n4. 记忆系统评审：总分 3/10，最大问题 context.json 从未被读取\n5. 两层设计更合理：hook 实时捕获（metadata only）+ session-summary LLM 提炼\n\n## 待跟进\n- [ ] 验证 session-summary 生成摘要文件\n- [ ] 验证 bootstrap 读取摘要注入新 session\n- [ ] 确认 ephemeral 内容被正确提炼\n\n<!-- source: agent:main:main -->\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776063349938}}
{"type":"message","id":"c10cd4c1","parentId":"9a371714","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:56:02.894Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This summary was generated at 13:00 UTC (21:00 GMT+8) today. That's the session before the current one. The session-summary hook IS working - it generated this summary. The question is whether bootstrap reads it.\n\nBut wait - the file exists at 13:00 UTC and the current session started at 06:48 UTC (14:48 GMT+8)... wait no, the current session started at 06:48 UTC according to the context. Let me check.\n\nActually looking at the session log:\n```\n{\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-13T06:48:43.961Z\",\"action\":\"new\",\"sessionKey\":\"agent:main:main\",...}\n```\n\nThat's 06:48 UTC = 14:48 GMT+8. And the session summary was from 13:00 UTC = 21:00 GMT+8, which is AFTER the /new. \n\nSo when the current session started at 14:48 GMT+8, the summary from 21:00 GMT+8 hadn't been created yet - that came from an earlier session that ended before this one even began. The session-summary hook worked correctly, generating summaries based on /new triggers, but the bootstrap handler.js should have injected the most recent summary into the current session's context. However, I have no way to verify what actually got injected since there's no session transcript to check against.\n\nLet me trace through what happened: the 2026-04-13-session-summary.md file was created by a session that ran from roughly 09:00 to 13:00 UTC, and when /new was triggered at 14:48 UTC to start the current session, bootstrap should have read that summary and injected it. The real problem is I can't confirm the injection happened because there's no output or transcript showing it. I should check the session history to see if the bootstrap actually processed the summary file correctly.","thinkingSignature":"9415aed977c58bd902ea4c300f6d6c1a0a68b0b6940d454b8803ad863e8458d8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_80998f5f34c24940b7c84526","name":"sessions_histo