 and when /new was triggered at 14:48 UTC to start the current session, bootstrap should have read that summary and injected it. The real problem is I can't confirm the injection happened because there's no output or transcript showing it. I should check the session history to see if the bootstrap actually processed the summary file correctly."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_80998f5f34c24940b7c84526","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"limit":5,"sessionKey":"agent:main:main"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776063349950,"responseId":"062bc675abbfae8e126f601a2d0aaf36","__openclaw":{"id":"c10cd4c1","seq":72}}],"truncated":true,"droppedMessages":false,"contentTruncated":true,"contentRedacted":false,"bytes":3561},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776063363040}}
{"type":"message","id":"547e7c37","parentId":"a842617f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:56:30.006Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see something interesting in the session history. The session started at 06:48 UTC (14:48 GMT+8) which is this current session. The session summary was generated at 13:00 UTC (21:00 GMT+8) which is from the NEXT session (after /new at 14:48, the session ran until about 21:00 GMT+8 when session-summary triggered on the /new that started the session after that).\n\nWait, let me re-read the session log. The current session started at 06:48 UTC (14:48 GMT+8). The session summary at 13:00 UTC (21:00 GMT+8) is from an even later session that ended after the current one was already running.\n \nI need to reconsider the session-summary hook's actual behavior. Looking at the HOOK.md, it's supposed to trigger on `command:new` or `command:reset` and generate a summary of the session that just ended. But the timestamps suggest the hook ran at 13:00 UTC for a session that ended after 14:48 GMT+8, which doesn't align with the expected sequence. This means either my timestamp interpretation is off, or the hook is triggering on a different event than I thought.\n\nLooking at the logs more carefully, when /new was called at 14:48 GMT+8 (06:48 UTC), it triggered session-summary to write the summary for the PREVIOUS session that had been running. The 13:00 UTC timestamp in the summary file is puzzling though—I need to figure out if that's when the session actually ended or if there's something else going on with how the timestamp got recorded. The summary file timestamp is 13:00 UTC, but the /new that triggered it happened at 06:48 UTC. Looking at the commands.log entry, that timestamp of 06:48:43 matches when /new was invoked. So the session-summary hook likely wrote the file at 06:48 UTC when processing the /new command, yet the file content shows 13:00 UTC instead—there's a discrepancy between when it was written and what timestamp appears in the file.\n\nNow examining the handler.js code, it extracts the current date and time using toISOString(), which gives UTC timestamps. When the session-summary hook ran at 06:48 UTC on April 13th, it would've generated \"2026-04-13T06:48:00.000Z\", making the date \"2026-04-13\" and time \"06:48\"—but the file shows \"13:00\" instead. The hook appears to be using a different time source or timezone than I initially thought.\n\nActually, I think the issue is simpler: the commands.log shows /new happened at 06:48 UTC, which corresponds to 14:48 GMT+8. But the session-summary file has timestamp 13:00 UTC (21:00 GMT+8)—that's a full 6 hours later. This suggests the summary was generated for an entirely different session, not the one that triggered at 06:48.\n\nLet me reconsider the timeline: the session ending at 13:00 UTC would have started around 09:00 UTC (17:00 GMT+8) on April 12th, run through the night, and ended with /new at 06:48 UTC on April 13th. When that /new triggered, it captured the summary from the session that had just concluded.\n\nBut I'm still puzzled by the timestamp mismatch—the summary shows 13:00 UTC yet the /new event was logged at 06:48 UTC. Let me check the actual file modification time to clarify what happened.\n\nLooking at the log entry more carefully, there's a ~6 hour gap between when /new was triggered at 06:48 UTC and when the summary was generated at 13:00 UTC. This suggests the session-summary hook might have processed the event with a significant delay, or there's something else creating this offset that I need to investigate further.\n\nThe most important finding is that the summary file exists and contains structured data from the previous session at 21:00 GMT+8, which means session-summary is functioning. The handler.js is correctly exporting the default function, and the hook triggers on /new events as expected.\n\nHowever, I should verify whether bootstrap actually reads and injects these summaries into the context. The handler.js implementation shows it pushes content to event.context.bootstrapFiles, but the session that ran at 06:48 UTC may have had different bootstrap behavior. Let me trace through the session history to confirm whether the summary was properly injected at that point.\n\nActually, re-reading the current session's greeting - it only says \"你好！我是小Claw\" without referencing any prior context, which suggests bootstrap either didn't inject the summary or the LLM didn't utilize it effectively. The session-summary hook generated the summary correctly, but there's a disconnect between what was generated and what actually gets used in the next session.\n\nI should focus on what I can actually fix: verifying the bootstrap handler is properly registered and working, ensuring session-summary can resolve the previous session file path from the event context, and making sure bootstrap reads from the right location. Let me run a test to confirm whether session-summary is even being invoked when /new is called.","thinkingSignature":"0d081fa38c5a76a95b624e95b68aae4faa7abaef0ed35adfd8ce3ec33d04566e"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n链路现状清楚了。问题是：**session-summary 写了这个文件**（2026-04-13-session-summary.md），但 bootstrap（handler.js）没有成功注入到当前 session。\n\n让我直接测试 /new 链路是否通：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dc3bdf58eba0450c9866f8a1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/ai/.openclaw && node -e \"\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\n\n// 模拟 bootstrap handler.js 的 getRecentSummaries 逻辑\nconst MEMORY_ROOT = '/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory';\nconst files = fs.readdirSync(MEMORY_ROOT);\nconst summaryFiles = files\n  .filter(f => (f.includes('summary') || f.match(/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}/)) && f.endsWith('.md'))\n  .filter(f => !f.startsWith('MEMORY'))\n  .sort()\n  .reverse()\n  .slice(0, 3);\nconsole.log('Summary files found:', summaryFiles);\n\nfor (const file of summaryFiles) {\n  const content = fs.readFileSync(path.join(MEMORY_ROOT, file), 'utf-8');\n  const hasSummaryOnly = content.includes('<!-- summary-only -->');\n  console.log(file, '- length:', content.length, '- has summary-only:', hasSummaryOnly, '- would inject:', hasSummaryOnly ? content.length < 2000 : true);\n}\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1317,"output":1395,"cacheRead":53184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55896,"cost":{"input":0.0003951,"output":0.001674,"cacheRead":0.0031910399999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00526014}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776063363051,"responseId":"062bc68183b5c441be06f098a767a10b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9dad24e3","parentId":"547e7c37","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:56:30.103Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_dc3bdf58eba0450c9866f8a1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary files found: [\n  '2026-04-13-无会话内容.md',\n  '2026-04-13-session-summary.md',\n  '2026-04-13-framework-fix.md'\n]\n2026-04-13-无会话内容.md - length: 166 - has summary-only: true - would inject: true\n2026-04-13-session-summary.md - length: 751 - has summary-only: true - would inject: true\n2026-04-13-framework-fix.md - length: 1496 - has summary-only: false - would inject: true"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":58,"aggregated":"Summary files found: [\n  '2026-04-13-无会话内容.md',\n  '2026-04-13-session-summary.md',\n  '2026-04-13-framework-fix.md'\n]\n2026-04-13-无会话内容.md - length: 166 - has summary-only: true - would inject: true\n2026-04-13-session-summary.md - length: 751 - has summary-only: true - would inject: true\n2026-04-13-framework-fix.md - length: 1496 - has summary-only: false - would inject: true","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776063390090}}
{"type":"message","id":"33cf4e36","parentId":"9dad24e3","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:56:45.401Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The bootstrap handler.js logic finds the summary files correctly. But the issue is: does the bootstrap hook actually fire on /new? And does it receive the `agent:bootstrap` event?\n\nThe problem might be that:\n1. The bootstrap event (`agent:bootstrap`) fires BEFORE the session starts processing messages\n2. But session-summary fires on `command:new` AFTER the session ends\n\nThese are two different hooks firing at different times:\n- `agent:bootstrap` → when the agent starts up (new session)\n- `command:new` → when user types /new (ends current session)\n\nSo the bootstrap (handler.js) SHOULD inject MEMORY.md and summaries when the session starts. \n\nThe summaries being injected should include content from previous sessions. But I'm not seeing evidence that bootstrap actually fired—the session started at 14:48 UTC (14:48 GMT+8) and I was able to greet the user and read files immediately, which means the SOUL.md startup sequence ran. The SOUL.md sequence reads SOUL.md, USER.md, today's and yesterday's memory files, MEMORY.md for main sessions, session context, and the most recent session summary. If bootstrap had injected MEMORY.md, I'd have seen it in the context at startup.\n\nLooking at the session summary files, `2026-04-13-session-summary.md` was created at 13:00 UTC and would be one of the 3 most recent summaries. If bootstrap had properly injected it, the session should have had access to that information, but it seems like it didn't get injected correctly.\n\nLet me trace through what actually happened: the user said \"可以用的吗\" (is it usable?) and I responded \"能用\" (it works). If the bootstrap had run with the summary information, I might have mentioned the session-summary or memory context, but I didn't. This suggests the bootstrap hook either didn't fire on /new, or it fired but didn't properly pass the session files to the new session context.\n\nI should check the openclaw logs to see what happened when /new was triggered, or test the /new command directly to verify if bootstrap is actually working. The real issue seems to be that session-summary fires after the command completes to generate the summary, while bootstrap fires on agent:bootstrap to inject content—but these might be two separate hooks that aren't communicating properly. handler.js only injects the MEMORY.md content, not the actual memory files themselves. The SOUL.md startup sequence loads context files, but there's no evidence that bootstrap actually injected anything when the current session started—the user immediately asked about memory and logs, suggesting the context wasn't present. I should verify whether bootstrap is even firing by checking if the handler.js file is registered as a hook in the system.","thinkingSignature":"17cdd74ed05d559b4e4f086908fa6285bcfb6c2a830673ef4764b0fdfffb0d14"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nhandler.js 找到了 3 个摘要文件且都会注入。问题可能在 bootstrap hook 根本没触发。让我检查一下：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_20c70608a71e429a95c939ad","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/ai/.openclaw -name \"*.json\" -path \"*/config/*\" 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l \"bootstrap\\|hook\" 2>/dev/null | head -5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a5052c3d6a4e4e9482420d50","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/.openclaw/config.json | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps({k:v for k,v in d.items() if 'hook' in k.lower() or 'bootstrap' in k.lower()}, indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":483,"output":741,"cacheRead":54464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55688,"cost":{"input":0.0001449,"output":0.0008891999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0032678399999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00430194}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776063390105,"responseId":"062bc69c27f4f623c41edd10