{"type":"message","id":"70ad678e","parentId":"0eac21b4","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:57:13.884Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture:\n\n1. `session-summary` hook is enabled in `openclaw.json` under `hooks.internal.entries`\n2. It should fire on `command:new` and `command:reset` events\n3. The hook handler.js is at `/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js`\n\nThe question is: does the hook actually fire on `/new` command? The session-summary.md file exists, so it has run at least once. But the summary file `2026-04-13-session-summary.md` was created at 13:00 UTC and the current session started at 06:48 UTC - so the summary was created by a session that ran AFTER the current session started.\n \nLet me reconsider the timeline. The current session is from agent:main:main with a /new at 06:48 UTC today, and there's a summary file from 13:00 UTC. That means the session before the current one ran from some point on April 12 through 13:00 UTC on April 13, creating that summary file.\n\nWhen the current session started at 06:48 UTC, bootstrap should have injected the most recent summary files, but since they were created at 13:00 UTC after that /new command, those particular summaries weren't available to inject yet. The files I'm seeing now were actually generated by a later session, which means the bootstrap injection during the current session's /new wouldn't have included them.\n\nThe real problem is that `previousSessionEntry` isn't populated in context.json, so session-summary can't read the actual previous session file to generate a proper summary. Instead it's only reading from ephemeral/*.jsonl files, which explains why the summaries are incomplete.\n\nTo properly test the memory chain, I need to verify that session-summary actually writes a summary file when triggered, then confirm whether bootstrap reads it correctly on the next session. But right now I can't verify the bootstrap read happened because there's no output or transcript showing what was injected. I should probably just document what I've found about the current state and let the user decide whether to do a fresh /new test to see the bootstrap output.","thinkingSignature":"90fc4b34d6cdfc6e83cdbabf87f94885b2cd9fd7e2a03ae4b2e14423af073620"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n找到了。断在 `context.json` 里 **没有 `previousSessionEntry` 字段**——这导致 session-summary 读不到旧 session 的消息内容，只能读 ephemeral。\n\n完整链路分析：\n\n**当前状态：**\n\n| 环节 | 状态 | 说明 |\n|------|------|------|\n| ephemeral 写入 | ✅ | auto-score-classify 在写 |\n| session-summary 触发 | ✅ | 写出了 `2026-04-13-session-summary.md` |\n| previousSessionEntry 注入 | ❌ | gateway 没传，旧 session 文件读不到 |\n| bootstrap handler.js | ✅ | 代码逻辑正确，能找到 3 个摘要文件 |\n| bootstrap 实际执行 | ❓ | 无法确认（无日志） |\n| LLM 上下文 | ❓ | 无法确认 |\n\n**真正的问题**：gateway 在 /new 时没有把 `previousSessionEntry.sessionFile` 传给 hook，所以 session-summary 只能基于 ephemeral 总结，失去了真正的会话内容。\n\n要完整验证记忆链路，需要一次新的 /new，看 bootstrap 注入的内容是否被 LLM 读取到。\n\n现在先做一件事：**验证 bootstrap 是否真的注入了 MEMORY.md 和摘要**——这需要看 /new 时有没有日志。\n\n你等一下，我直接发一条 /new 的测试命令来验证：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1f99fa28b1dd4ffd95080801","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway status 2>/dev/null | head -5; ps aux | grep -E \"gateway|node\" | grep -v grep | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":215,"output":761,"cacheRead":56064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57040,"cost":{"input":0.0000645,"output":0.0009132,"cacheRead":0.00336384,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00434154}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776063415442,"responseId":"062bc6b6fcc81cf1012ef0cb775d57d2"}}
