{"type":"message","id":"904bc532","parentId":"53cd9b74","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:57:25.802Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see:\n- `openclaw-router/context-api.js` running (PID 434)\n- `dist/main.js` running (PID 577) - this is the gateway\n\nThe gateway is running. The issue is that the bootstrap hook (handler.js) should fire on `agent:bootstrap` event when a new session starts.\n\nThe session-summary hook fires on `command:new` and `command:reset`. When /new is triggered:\n1. session-summary hook fires → tries to read previousSessionEntry.sessionFile → but sessionFile might be null\n2. bootstrap hook fires → injects MEMORY.md and summaries into context.bootstrapFiles\n\nBut I couldn't verify if bootstrap actually ran because there's no session transcript showing the injected content.\n\n\nThe real problem is that `previousSessionEntry` isn't being populated in context.json when /new is called, so session-summary can't access the previous session's data. I should test this by triggering /new and checking the logs to see if bootstrap actually runs.","thinkingSignature":"528e10491b274defb38fd029bd421e6fcad5b8b272fd2d18ac5b505f9d0f1316"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_116ed038867f43e1aff0d181","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/.openclaw/logs/commands.log | tail -20; find /home/ai/.openclaw -name \"*.log\" -newer /home/ai/.openclaw/logs/commands.log 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1571,"output":283,"cacheRead":57280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59134,"cost":{"input":0.00047129999999999996,"output":0.00033959999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0034368,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0042477}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776063437630,"responseId":"062bc6cc68a77f624eb03fac2599e8ed"}}
